<subSubSection id="25AD655A13175C49FF15FEC2CE12FE4F" pageId="19" pageNumber="472" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="6D0836D113175C49FF15FEC2C966FE2F" blockId="19.[174,1232,351,506]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">
Distribution. Widespread European species (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013175C49FCD0FEC2C932FECF" author="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M." box="[806,1063,351,378]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472" refId="ref19613" refString="Papp, L. &amp; Cerny, M. 2015. Agromyzidae (Diptera) of Hungary. Volume 1. Agromyzinae. Nagykovacsi, Pars Ltd., 1 - 416. DOI: http: // doi. org / 10.18655 / Agromyzidae. Vol. 1." type="book" year="2015">Papp &amp; Černý, 2015</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313175C49FBC8FEC2C9C5FECC" bold="true" box="[1086,1232,351,377]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">
In 
<collectingCountry id="15A0764113175C49FB93FEC2C9DEFECC" box="[1125,1227,351,377]" name="Ukraine" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313175C49FF58FEE2CC04FE2C" box="[174,273,383,409]" country="Ukraine" name="Donets'k" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">Donetsk</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313175C49FEBDFEE2CCBFFE2C" box="[331,426,383,409]" country="Ukraine" name="Kharkiv" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">Kharkiv</collectingRegion>
Regions (
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013175C49FDEBFEE2CFA9FE2C" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[541,700,383,409]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472" pagination="61 - 68" refId="ref19059" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2011. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 1. 28 new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 19 (2), 61 - 68 [In Russian]." type="journal article" year="2011">Guglya, 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="09264B2013175C49FD31FEE2CE11FE2F" author="Guglya, Yu." box="[711,772,383,410]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472" pagination="29 - 38" refId="ref19304" refString="Guglya, Yu. 2015. A study of the fauna of leaf-miner flies of the subfamily Agromyzinae (Diptera: Agromyzidae) of Ukraine. Report 3. Eleven new species for the fauna of Ukraine. The Kharkov Entomological Society Gazette, 23 (2), 29 - 38." type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
); 
<collectingRegion id="AF73F83313175C49FCE0FEE2CEDDFE2C" box="[790,968,383,409]" country="Ukraine" name="Zakarpattya" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">Transcarpathia</collectingRegion>
(
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313175C49FC2CFEE2C977FE2C" bold="true" box="[986,1122,383,409]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">first record</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D0836D113175C49FF15FE02CE12FE4F" blockId="19.[174,1232,351,506]" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">
Bionomics. This species is related to 
<taxonomicName id="AAB74D5213175C49FD50FE3DCE5CFE0C" authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1835" box="[678,841,416,442]" class="Insecta" family="Agromyzidae" genus="Agromyza" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="19" pageNumber="472" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cinerascens">
<emphasis id="5FC3EAC313175C49FD50FE3DCE5CFE0C" box="[678,841,416,442]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="472">A. cinerascens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and both often occur together in the same biotopes. Only one generation develops per year, adults can be collected from late April to early May, and larvae develop during May.
</paragraph>
